Acer launched a new lineup of Predator gaming monitors at CES 2020 which includes a cutting-edge 4K OLED gaming display. The company unveiled its new Predator CG552K, Predator X38, and Predator X32 displays at the event, stating that these monitors offer a premium experience and cater to a variety of gamers. “Acer has gone big with its premium Predator gaming monitors, offering expansive views with cutting-edge technologies that support true-to-life gameplay, even with the most demanding of titles,” said Acer Digital Display Business President Victor Chien. “We support gamers of all types from novices to professionals with some of the best performing gaming hardware on the market.” Below are all the details of the new Acer Predator gaming monitors unveiled at CES 2020. The Predator CG552K is the highlight of Acer’s new monitor lineup thanks to its cutting-edge OLED display and powerful features. This display boasts a 55-inch OLED panel with a resolution of 3,840 x 2,160, as well as support for G-Sync and adaptive refresh rate technology. The panel also offers 400 nits of brightness and 98.5% coverage of the DCI-P3 colour gamut, which means it is capable of delivering an impressive viewing experience along with smooth gameplay. “Both Adaptive Sync and Nvidia G-Sync Compatible, the Predator CG552K provides smooth gameplay and helps gamers stay focused,” Acer said. “It also lets them make every second count with up to an incredibly fast 0.5 ms (G to G) response time via overdrive and a 120Hz refresh rate.” A built-in light sensor detects the brightness of the room the monitor is placed in and adjusts the levels of the screen accordingly. It also has a proximity sensor which it can use to automatically wake up when a person is nearby. Connectivity options include three HDMI 2.0 ports, two DisplayPort v1.4 ports, and one USB Type-C port, as well as two USB 2.0 and USB 3.0 ports. The Predator CG552K also includes a pair of 10W speakers and customizable light strips. Acer said the Predator CG552K gaming monitor will be available in Q3 2020 starting at $2,999. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-334140" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Acer-Predator-CG552K.jpg" alt="Acer Predator CG552K" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Acer-Predator-CG552K.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Acer-Predator-CG552K-595x400.jpg 595w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Acer-Predator-CG552K-300x202.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-334138" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Acer-Predator-CG552K-1.jpg" alt="Acer Predator CG552K 1" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Acer-Predator-CG552K-1.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Acer-Predator-CG552K-1-595x400.jpg 595w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Acer-Predator-CG552K-1-300x202.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Alongside its flagship OLED display, Acer also announced two smaller gaming monitors – the Predator X38 and Predator X32. The X38 and X32 monitors have 37.5-inch and 32-inch panel sizes respectively, and both include support for Nvidia’s G-Sync refresh rate technology. These monitors also boast impressive image quality with high screen resolutions and VESA DisplayHDR certifications. The Predator X32 has a resolution of 3,840 x 2,160 and a refresh rate of 144Hz, while the Predator X38 has a resolution of 3,840 x 1,600 with a refresh rate of up to 175Hz. Both devices are fitted with various connectivity options, as well as stereo speaker configurations. The Predator X32 will be available in Q2 2020 from $3,599, while the Predator X38 will be available in April 2020 from $2,399. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-334142" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Acer-Predator-X32-1.jpg" alt="Acer Predator X32 1" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Acer-Predator-X32-1.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Acer-Predator-X32-1-595x400.jpg 595w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Acer-Predator-X32-1-300x202.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-334150" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Acer-Predator-X32-3.jpg" alt="Acer Predator X32 3" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Acer-Predator-X32-3.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Acer-Predator-X32-3-595x400.jpg 595w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Acer-Predator-X32-3-300x202.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-334148" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Acer-Predator-X38-2.jpg" alt="Acer Predator X38 2" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Acer-Predator-X38-2.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Acer-Predator-X38-2-595x400.jpg 595w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Acer-Predator-X38-2-300x202.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-334146" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Acer-Preda